&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love This Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As an Account Executive you will be part of a regional sales team and the overall face of Newsela in the small-medium business market. You’ll be responsible for building relationships with key decision makers at the school district level in addition to selling Newsela’s suite of products to bring engaging reading content to districts. In your day to day, you will do everything from pipeline management and forecasting, to designing lead generation campaigns and managing sales through the entire lifecycle. You will also become well-versed in your territory’s funding, state initiatives, demographics, and K-12 education landscape, which will help inform your overall sales strategy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;While this is a remote position, the role manages our Western territory. To best support our clients and team, candidates must reside within the Western United States (Pacific or Mountain Time Zones).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Preferred Locations: Washington, Oregon, California, Colorado, New Mexico, and Arizona. &lt;/em&gt;Open to nearby states as long as you are able to work on Pacific/Mountain time&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;zone(s). &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As an individual contributor who is part of a regional sales team, you will have the opportunity to own your territory, manage the entire lifecycle of a sale, and build new business relationships that bring Newsela’s solutions to classrooms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Take ownership of developing territory business plans, evaluating funding landscapes, and tailoring sales strategies to align with district initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;In addition to achieving your own revenue targets, you will get to work with an enthusiastic, cross-functional team to catapult Newsela’s growth as we scale our national sales organization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Meet in-person with school and district leaders, presenting solutions, negotiating terms, and securing agreements that bring Newsela into classrooms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Have a direct impact on the expansion and adoption of Newsela products, which will ultimately scale Newsela’s ability to bring engaging, culturally responsive learning content to K-12 classrooms nationwide.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love This Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Assessment Services team at Newsela works with strategic and key accounts supporting customer assessment needs end to end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Assessment Services Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;is a hands-on individual contributor role focused on delivering high-quality assessment services to assigned accounts. You’ll work day-to-day with district and school stakeholders and help turn assessment expertise into real customer value.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support implementation &amp;amp; onboarding. &lt;/strong&gt;Help stand up Newsela’s assessment products for assigned accounts, including onboarding, configuration, and go-live support. Be the steady hand customers can count on during launch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver ongoing advisory &amp;amp; support. &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with customers to deepen their use of Newsela assessments. This may include score interpretation, surfacing additional assessment needs, data coaching, and usage reviews that drive renewal-worthy outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute assessment migration &amp;amp; content work. &lt;/strong&gt;Carry out assessment migration and content services for assigned accounts with attention to scope, quality, and timelines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own your accounts. &lt;/strong&gt;Manage your portfolio of customer engagements end-to-end: scope, schedule, communicate, and deliver. Escalate early when something needs help.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Document and improve. &lt;/strong&gt;Capture what works in playbooks, templates, and reusable artifacts so the team gets stronger with every engagement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner cross-functionally. &lt;/strong&gt;Work side-by-side with Customer Service, Sales, Product, and Content. Be a reliable, easy-to-work-with teammate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be a voice of the customer. &lt;/strong&gt;Bring patterns and signal from your customer work back to the team. Evidence over anecdotes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love This Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As a Sales Development Representative (SDR) you will work across Newsela’s Sales organization to support aggressive growth by researching, prospecting through calls and emails, and qualifying leads in order to build pipeline for Sales Reps. Your days will be composed of responding to inbound inquiries, proactive cold outreach to potential new customers, and providing online product demonstrations that draw prospects into initial discovery calls and identify key needs that ultimately lead to qualified opportunities for our Sales team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Collaborate within the Sales organization to inform strategy and processes that enhance overall sales performance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Thrive within a highly supportive team environment, backed by robust sales training, enablement, marketing, and operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Act as the initial point of contact with prospects, representing the future of education, enhancing how districts and teachers engage students, and providing approaches that allow educators to design customized learning for different reading levels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Gather insights and feedback from the market to directly influence and drive future product enhancements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Drive high-volume outbound prospecting through a strategic blend of automated and highly personalized email cadences, along with targeted daily phone outreach to school’s key decision makers, including school administrators and instructional coaches.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Partner closely with a dedicated Account Executive (AE) to align on territory strategy, coordinate outreach, and seamlessly book introductory meetings with qualified prospects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Collaborate with the SDR team to review calls, share what’s working with one another, and continuously iterate on outreach strategies, crafting scripts and customized talk tracks that deliver the messaging that resonates best within the market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love This Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Reporting to the Senior Manager, Deal Desk, the Senior Deal Desk Analyst will administer and assist in optimizing key processes following best practices in a way that scales with Newsela&#39;s growth and sets the company up for future success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively across different functions to comprehend the deal standards, structure, business terms, and identification of potential risks and/or opportunities that can affect performance, growth, and strategic positioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and provide input as to the critical information to move the deal forward, such as the summary of discussions, decisions made, and assigned actions to be completed during Deal Desk Committee meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a subject matter expert on policies, approval frameworks, contract constructs, and revenue implications, providing support to Sales and cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence cross-functional stakeholders and drive resolution of complex deal issues, serving as an escalation point for high-impact opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage collaboration with cross-functional stakeholders, including Contracts/Legal, Revenue Accounting, Sales and Finance to review or address revenue recognition concerns for non-standard deal structures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide post-execution support, helping resolve issues between Sales, Revenue Accounting, and Order Management teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a valued advisor to Sales on deals by providing guidance on best practices for deal management and contract structuring and drive deal closure by being approachable and providing direct support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify recurring issues, bottlenecks, and quality gaps in deal execution. Recommend process improvements and opportunities for automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be creative and solutions-oriented. You will be empowered to find solutions to non-standard opportunities that still align with business rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop an in-depth understanding of Sales process and Salesforce platform to help identify opportunities to improve key sales metrics and overall process gaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience working within Deal Desk, Finance, Sales Operations, or Revenue Operations functions, with a focus on deal review, approvals, contract structuring, revenue recognition considerations, and cross-functional sales support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to partner effectively across functions and levels throughout the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess problems in a structured fashion and identify key issues to solve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy, coupled with big-picture strategic comprehension.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under ambiguity and multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work well under pressure, with intense prioritization along with timely and transparent communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Salesforce, Adobe, Word, Excel and Google suite. CPQ experiences a bonus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English (written and verbal) required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness (and ideally experience) working US based hours (PHL night shift)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hours: 8 hours a day Monda

